<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="63" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,152,522]" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,309,324,348]" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">Remarks.</emphasis>
The morphology of the aedeagus of 
<taxonomicName box="[733,854,325,348]" class="Insecta" family="Hydrochidae" genus="Hydrochus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="farsicus">
<emphasis box="[733,854,325,348]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">H. farsicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
resembles that of some Iberian species (
<taxonomicName authority="Valladares, Diaz &amp; Delgado" authorityName="Valladares, Diaz &amp; Delgado" class="Insecta" family="Hydrochidae" genus="Hydrochus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ibericus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">Hydrochus ibericus</emphasis>
Valladares, Díaz &amp; Delgado
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Valladares" authorityName="Valladares" box="[620,858,360,383]" class="Insecta" family="Hydrochidae" genus="Hydrochus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="angusi">
<emphasis box="[620,729,360,383]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">H. angusi</emphasis>
Valladares
</taxonomicName>
), although it may also be related to the group of 
<taxonomicName authority="Schaller" authorityName="Schaller" class="Insecta" family="Hydrochidae" genus="Hydrochus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="elongatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">H. elongatus</emphasis>
(Schaller)
</taxonomicName>
, with a more eastern distribution (Hidalgo-Galiana 
<emphasis box="[914,960,394,417]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">et al</emphasis>
., in preparation). 
<bibRefCitation box="[1149,1336,394,417]" pageId="2" pageNumber="64" refString="Mart, A., Incekara, U., Polat, A. &amp; Karaka, H. (2009) Hydrochus ibericus and Hydrochus nodulifer, two new records for the Hydrochidae (Coleoptera) fauna of Turkey. Turkish Journal of Zoology, 33, 249 - 250." type="journal article">
Mart 
<emphasis box="[1207,1253,394,417]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">et al</emphasis>
. (
<number box="[1273,1329,394,417]" pageId="2" pageNumber="63" value="2009.0">2009</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
recorded 
<taxonomicName box="[151,270,429,452]" class="Insecta" family="Hydrochidae" genus="Hydrochus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ibericus">
<emphasis box="[151,270,429,452]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">H. ibericus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[336,413,429,452]" name="Turkey" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">Turkey</collectingCountry>
, but unfortunately they did not figure the aedeagus and did not give details of the material used for comparison.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
